4 SJR___ COMMENDING MACKENZIE GRACE STIGILE ON HER
5 ACCOMPLISHMENTS.
6
7 WHEREAS, reading is a foundational skill that fosters
8 imagination, critical thinking, empathy, and lifelong
9 learning; and
10 WHEREAS, Mackenzie Grace Stigile, at the age of 20
11 months, has demonstrated extraordinary dedication,
12 curiosity, and perseverance by reading, with assistance,
13 3,500 children's books in 2025, an achievement far exceeding
14 typical expectations for a young child; and
15 WHEREAS, this remarkable accomplishment reflects not
16 only an exceptional love of learning, but also discipline,
17 focus, and a commitment to personal growth; and
18 WHEREAS, Mackenzie Grace's family has proudly watched
19 her vocabulary grow and develop; she often starts using new
20 words that she has learned from books within a few hours of
21 reading them; at 20 months old, she can independently say
22 her alphabet and numbers one through 20; identify her
23 letters, colors, and animals accurately; and often speaks in
24 full sentences and phrases; and
25 WHEREAS, the majority of her reading is done at home
26 or at her mother's office with her mother and grandmother;
27 the family's personal book collection includes childhood
28 favorites of her mother's and a few contributions from
Page 1

favorites of her mother's and a few contributions from
SJR31 Enrolled
29 cousins; however, the Stigile family also makes frequent
30 trips to the public library to check out extra books, and
31 Mackenzie Grace further enjoys receiving the Dolly Parton
32 Imagination Library books; and
33 WHEREAS, the Stigile family's main goals for
34 Mackenzie Grace are early language, communication, and
35 literacy; as these skills are fundamental to a solid
36 foundation, her parents want to ensure she has the best
37 possible education they can provide; her family also
38 believes that success starts at home; and
39 WHEREAS, during 2026, the Stigile family hopes to
40 read 4,000 books and begin working on sight words with
41 Mackenzie Grace; and
42 WHEREAS, Mackenzie Grace serves as an inspiration to
43 peers, families, educators, and the broader community by
44 showing that reading can be both joyful and transformative;
45 now therefore,
46 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA, BOTH
47 HOUSES THEREOF CONCURRING, That Mackenzie Grace Stigile is
48 hereby commended for this outstanding literary achievement,
49 and this resolution is presented to the Stigile family as a
50 symbol of pride, encouragement, and appreciation for this
51 historic accomplishment.
